  "text": "The Rust borrow checker's MIR analysis chain begins with the mir_borrowck query entry point in compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/lib.rs (line 117), which delegates to BorrowCheckRootCtxt::do_mir_borrowck in compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/root_cx.rs (line 242).\n\nThe key phase is borrowck_collect_region_constraints (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/lib.rs:309), which orchestrates the entire analysis:\n\n1. **MIR Region Replacement** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/nll.rs:56): The replace_regions_in_mir function rewrites regions in the MIR to use NLL (Non-Lexical Lifetimes) variables, enabling flow-sensitive lifetime analysis.\n\n2. **Borrow Set Construction** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/borrow_set.rs:169): BorrowSet::build gathers all borrows by traversing the MIR with the GatherBorrows visitor. This identifies borrow locations, kinds, and regions. Two-phase borrows are tracked via the TwoPhaseActivation enum (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/borrow_set.rs:66), which marks reservation and activation points.\n\n3. **MIR Type Checking** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/type_check/mod.rs:98): The type_check function performs complete type-checking on MIR and generates region constraints between different lifetimes.\n\n4. **Live Range Calculation** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/type_check/liveness/mod.rs:29 and compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/type_check/liveness/trace.rs:40): The generate and trace functions implement liveness analysis. The trace function performs a reverse depth-first search through the MIR from variable uses to compute which regions must be live at which CFG points. This determines the live range of each region by analyzing both USE-LIVE sets (from uses) and DROP-LIVE sets (from drops).\n\n5. **Place Conflict Detection** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/places_conflict.rs): The places_conflict (line 81) and borrow_conflicts_with_place (line 104) functions determine if two places conflict by comparing projections in lockstep. This is essential for detecting when a borrow conflicts with an access, using PlaceConflictBias to handle ambiguous index comparisons conservatively.\n\n6. **Region Inference** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/nll.rs:113): The compute_regions function creates a RegionInferenceContext and manages polonius facts (if enabled). It then calls RegionInferenceContext::solve (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/region_infer/mod.rs:493), which solves all region constraints via constraint propagation and type checking to determine final region values.\n\n7. **Two-Phase Borrow Resolution** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/lib.rs:1823): The check_activations method implements two-phase borrow checking. At activation points, it verifies that two-phase borrows don't interfere with other live borrows. Two-phase borrows act as shared borrows from reservation to activation point, then as mutable borrows afterward, allowing patterns like v.push(&mut v[0]).\n\nThe complete flow chains these components together: entry point → root context → constraint collection → region replacement → borrow gathering → type checking → liveness analysis → conflict detection → region solving → two-phase resolution, ensuring soundness of the borrow checker."
}

